treatment.paragraph:
Preorbital stripe blackish, running from upper lip to orbit; more or less masked by dark snout pigmentation. Postorbital stripe composed of dark blotch immediately posterior to orbit and two parallel, partly confluent stripes on opercle. Suborbital stripe running from infraorbital 3 obliquely caudoventrad toward preopercular margin, usually ending before reaching preopercular margin; uniformly pigmented proximally but distally breaking up into dots, one on each scale crossed by stripe; rarely confined to spot at orbital margin (
Fig. 2
).
